cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.DC 

This paper is primarily focused on the networking aspect of femtocells and their impact on cellular networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes an auction-based incentive framework, which falls under the category of game theory and mechanism design. Hence, cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also a likely category. The paper also involves information theory and communication theory, which are covered under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper discusses security and privacy concerns related to femtocells, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper involves some computational complexity analysis, which is covered under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
